The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bangla win ODI series
                                                     Bangla win ODI series
                  MoM Mortaza                     
	Dhaka: Bangladesh comfortably beat Zimbabwe by six wickets on Friday to clinch the three-game ODI series 2-1.         
	In a match reduced to 37 overs per side, Zimbabwe was sent in and they recorded 119/9. Bangladesh reached 121/4 with more than four overs to spare. Shakib Al Hasan Hasan was named player of the series with Mashrafe bin Mortaza bagging the Man of the Match honours.           (AP)                                                                                                                   
